OL,3,CIsland's doctors claim health service
OL,4,Cis 'poor place to work'
OL,6,FIn a free text section of the survey,
OL,7,Fone doctor said, "Senior managers need
OL,8,Fto come and follow a shift on Monday
OL,9,Fmorning in theatres to experience how
OL,10,Fthe system is failing patients."
OL,12,FAnother said: "Doesn't matter. No one
OL,13,Fis going to listen. It's pointless
OL,14,Fmentioning anything."
OL,16,FDoctors said they felt 'over-stretched
OL,17,Fand under-resourced', with 67%
OL,18,Fbelieving they do not have the
OL,19,Fresources they need to do a good job,
OL,20,Fand only 20% agreeing that they have
OL,21,Fsufficient time to do their job well.
