OL,3,CIsland's doctors claim health service
OL,4,Cis 'poor place to work'
OL,6,F"The BMA is committed to working with
OL,7,FManx doctors to help them organise and
OL,8,Fadvocate for themselves in their
OL,9,Fworkplace ` we hope the management of
OL,10,FManx Care are ready to work with us."
OL,12,FDr Thiagarajan added: "Following
OL,13,Fprevious barometer of care surveys
OL,14,Fwe've been hopeful that poor results
OL,15,Fcould act as a catalyst for change,
OL,16,Fbut after this third set of results
OL,17,Fshowing that doctors are frustrated,
OL,18,Foverworked, and crucially, don't feel
OL,19,Flistened to, we're losing faith that
OL,20,FManx Care has the will to change
OL,21,Fthings.
